        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=12174&TOPIC_ID=1693&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Hell+Levels&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Here is my thoughts.  Even if you didn't need more exp to get to 50 because the exp was dstributed, I seriously doubt people would lvl faster.  <BR>Think about it.. you are low lvl again and you get to lvl 40. Woohoo, it's a hell lvl.  You spent the last month ( cause this is your highest char ) getting from 36 to 40 and it took a lot of hard work.. but you made it at a timely pace of a couple hours each night.  Now your in 40 hell, what are you going to do about it?  Your going to bust your ass and quit sleeping to get through that lvl to 41.<BR>  People see hell lvls as a challenege and they respond by getting through them as quick as they can.. and often times they do it faster ( I mean this in the sense that maybe they would take there time with a normal level and finish it in a week or so, but with hell lvls, they spend a few all-nighters ) than they would a normal lvl.  <BR>I know this was true for me when lvling... I would spend a little time each day getting exp.. but when a hell lvl came around, I would bust my ass night and day trying to get through it... the result is because of the modivation I would spend more time and finish faster.<BR>   Now of course, this says nothing for the amnount of time spent in game.. which is how you learn to be better at the game.  But on the same hand, I wouldn't expect to see every noob lvl 50 by next week either.<BR>    This is just my thoughts, you don't need to flame them because I never contridicted your thoughts :)</P><P>Zaranil Shadowfiend<BR>56 Defiler of Kotiz<BR>Terris Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
